The VP was modeled as an end-point impedance that subjects interacted with using a small robotic manipulandum (GeoMagic Touch, 3D Systems, Andover MA). Full details of the model, which was based on previously collected data on stroke survivors12, are reported in Hasson and Goodman11. Using this stroke survivor data, a reference VP kinematic trajectory was specified (Fig. 1; red trajectory). The step pattern associated with this reference trajectory (representing the affected leg) had a smaller step height and width compared to the unaffected leg. When subjects applied a force that made the manipulandum deviate from the reference trajectory, they experienced an impedance force FIMP as1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
